{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":259817,"duration_api_ms":254188,"num_turns":2,"result":"## core_business_v2 Ingestion Module\n\n### Overview\n\nThe ingestion module is a Spring Boot service that processes entity ingestion requests (hosts, user-host bindings) through a multi-stage pipeline: **Label → Policy → Enforcement**. It uses Redis streams for async message processing, distributed locks for concurrency, and a fingerprint-based deduplication strategy.\n\n---\n\n### REST Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/ingestion/events` | Main ingestion entry point — accepts `IngestionRequest`, publishes to Redis stream, waits up to 60s for result |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/entities/query` | Query failed entities with pagination (`EntityQueryDTO`) |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/entities/{id}` | Get entity by ID |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/entities/{id}/display-status` | Get display status (init/running/enforced/failed) |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/fingerprint/calculate` | Calculate fingerprint for given entity attributes |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/policy/apply-existing-entities` | Mark all entities for reprocessing |\n\n---\n\n### Request Processing Flow\n\n```\nClient POST /api/v1/ingestion/events\n  │\n  ▼\nIngestionController (127 lines)\n  ├── Generate requestId + traceId\n  ├── Register CompletableFuture in CallbackRegistry (60s timeout)\n  ├── Publish IngestionRequest to Redis INGESTION_INTERNAL_STREAM\n  └── Wait for future completion on nettyOffloadExecutor\n        │\n        ▼\nIngestionInternalConsumer (181 lines) — Redis stream consumer\n  │\n  ▼\nIngestionOrchestrator.process(req) (107 lines)\n  ├── 1. Cache lookup: EntityCache.getCachedEntityId(key)\n  │     ├── HIT  → CachedExistingEntityHandler\n  │     └── MISS → Acquire CREATE_LOCK\n  │\n  ├── 2. DB lookup (under lock)\n  │     ├── Found → DbExistingEntityHandler → CachedExistingEntityHandler\n  │     └── Not found → NewEntityHandler\n  │\n  ▼\nHandler Selection (fingerprint comparison + lock state):\n  ┌─────────────────────┬────────────────┬──────────────────────┐\n  │                     │ Lock Acquired  │ Lock Not Acquired    │\n  ├─────────────────────┼────────────────┼──────────────────────┤\n  │ Same Fingerprint    │ Return as-is   │ Poll until done      │\n  │ Different Fingerprint│ Reset + run SM │ Interrupt + retry    │\n  │                     │                │ lock + reset + run SM│\n  └─────────────────────┴────────────────┴──────────────────────┘\n  │\n  ▼\nEntityStateMachine.start() (336 lines)\n  │\n  PENDING ──[LabelService]──→ LABELED\n  LABELED ──[PolicyService]──→ EVALUATED\n  EVALUATED ──[EnforcementService]──→ ENFORCED\n  │\n  Each stage: up to 3 retries with exponential backoff (1s×attempt + jitter)\n  Retryable vs non-retryable codes determine whether to retry or fail\n  DB updated after each stage transition\n  │\n  ▼\nConsumer completes the CallbackRegistry future → Controller returns ResultDTO to client\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Classes & Responsibilities\n\n**Controllers:**\n- `IngestionController` — async ingest via Redis stream + callback future\n- `EntityController` — entity queries and status display\n- `PolicyController` — trigger bulk reprocessing\n\n**Orchestration:**\n- `IngestionOrchestrator` — routes requests: cache hit → existing handler, cache miss → lock → DB lookup → new/existing handler\n- `IngestionInternalConsumer` / `IngestionExternalConsumer` — Redis stream consumers\n\n**Handlers (4 fingerprint cases):**\n- `SameAttributesWithLockAcquiredHandler` — no-op, entity unchanged\n- `SameAttributesWithLockNotAcquiredHandler` — poll until processing finishes\n- `DifferentAttributesWithLockAcquiredHandler` — reset entity, run state machine\n- `DifferentAttributesWithLockNotAcquiredHandler` — interrupt running SM, acquire lock, reset, run SM\n\n**State Machine:**\n- `EntityStateMachine` — drives PENDING→LABELED→EVALUATED→ENFORCED with retry logic\n- `EntityStageTransactionRunner` — wraps each stage call in `@Transactional`\n\n**Services (stage executors):**\n- `LabelService` — calls RuleEngineService for labeling\n- `PolicyService` — policy evaluation (currently placeholder)\n- `EnforcementService` — enforcement (currently placeholder)\n\n**Utilities:**\n- `EntityCache` — Redis-backed cache for entity IDs (Redisson `RBucket`)\n- `EntityUtil` — SHA256 fingerprint from 40+ host fields, 34 user fields, 2 dynamic client fields\n- `RedisUtil` — lock key generation per entity type\n\n**Background Jobs:**\n- `PolicyReprocessJob` (364 lines) — batch reprocessing of entities marked INIT\n- `StuckEntityRecoveryJob` (229 lines) — recovers entities stuck in intermediate states\n\n---\n\n### Architectural Patterns\n\n1. **Async request/response** — REST call → Redis stream → consumer processes → completes `CompletableFuture` → REST returns\n2. **Fingerprint deduplication** — SHA256 of entity attributes determines if reprocessing is needed\n3. **Two-tier locking** — `CREATE_LOCK` (entity creation, fast-fail) + `PROCESS_LOCK` (state machine execution, supports spin-retry & interruption)\n4. **Graceful degradation** — cache miss falls through to DB; cache write failure degrades to DB-only mode\n5. **Delay queue** — failed requests requeued to Redis sorted set with exponential backoff","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d22d128b-a0bc-4069-aae6-594fe0304d09","total_cost_usd":0.7004574500000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21786,"cache_read_input_tokens":36931,"output_tokens":1843,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":21786,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":1843,"cacheReadInputTokens":36931,"cacheCreationInputTokens":21786,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.20072299999999998,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":118,"outputTokens":20746,"cacheReadInputTokens":2430377,"cacheCreationInputTokens":122279,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.49973445000000005,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_012E3AkwjJjoE5zUeStRx6Qr","tool_input":{"command":"for f in /Users/zliu/IdeaProjects/FortiNAC/core_business_v2/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/**/*.java; do echo \"$(wc -l < \"$f\") $(basename \"$f\")\"; done | sort -rn | head -30"}}],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"1d4212e9-0e56-4089-93f3-dc0a54a902a9"}
